text: <@U4V5EHQ2G> I think your judge friend gave you some bad info. When a creature is destroyed with Decree of Pain, regardless of where it ends up, you draw the cards. I'll tag <@U340CHVJA> here, but I double checked with judge chat this morning.
Decree of Pain doesn't check for death triggers, only to see if the creatures were destroyed, which is different.
Correct, decree only cares that it is destroyed, not dies, so where you don't get cards is from indestructible cards
Or regenerated creatures
So we had it right originally
Yes.

You know, I've been thinking about becoming a judge. In order to do so I need to judge two RELs first. Easy enough...

And that's when I realized that Unstable is coming out. I guess I'll try judging when RIX is out, there's no way I'll be able to judge Unstable...
it wouldnt count anyways
its not REL
its casual
:stuck_out_tongue:
Playing two games against Kess, one against Inala and one against Mairisil last night cemented what I had suspected all allong . . . I fucking detest the wizards deck
Or the commanders at least
Specifically?
I've yet to play one that wasn't just five minute turns watching a dude masturbate with uncommon wizards whose art I don't recognize
Kess and Mairsil should not be that slow and grindy.
Well, Mairsil depends on the build, I suppose.
"So first I'm gonna tutor up this Panharmonicon, then I cast archeomancer to bring back whatever, making a copy of archeomaner which brings back this thing to get this guy to copy this."
Didn't help it was like four games in a row to be fair
So would it be better if they were uncommon wizards whose art you did recognize?
Would be less annoying than having to read every shitty Khans wizard I've never bothered to look at
That kind play can be fun, too. You're doing a lot of shit. Just that many games in a row of it and not just from the same person was just numbing
But now you've learned something new.
Just kill them first...isn't that the old <@U4V5EHQ2G> rule? :wink:
Just picture them a hug deck
That was my solution last night. Make all the wizards you want, a berserked overran Silvos with Heroic Intervention backup kills you just the same
I also learned you just can't let Ramos exist
Oh no, yeah, Ramos must be destroyed on sight.
Ramos is the ultimate 'hidden commander' general.
"wanna do any broken shit you could possibly want? Build Ramos"
He supports any and all colors and just makes you free mana to fuel your combos
Ah, Dana, my Jess deck is just nekusar with a couple of enchantments switched out because no one wants nekusar out
Fairly effective
I wound up getting crushed by a Ramos/Jeskai Ascendancy/Sprout Swarm combo
He's the easiest 5-color commander to cast.
Oh, you can pay the buyback cost via convoke, can't you...that's dirty.
That kind of combo I can't complain about losing to
That's a lot of moving pieces, one of which requires you to be running Sprout Swarm
Well that's great
A funny design, but this is exactly the card I’ll be using as an example when people ask why Un-cards aren’t legal in Commander
It's like a better O-Stone
It only hits one person, but it’ll hit their everything
Only things not touching this thing
Oh, wait.
Wow. That's a hard lock after it fills up, actually. That's about as fun as Clocknapper
This unset looks pretty oppressive, actually
Unfair.
It fills up and then sacs itself dean
Oh, missed the self sac part
Sac vs exile so plenty of ways to have more fun.
Yuppers
At least they avoided destroying itself so you can just keep it there when indestructible
They've learned since Nev's Disk
<@U3L7A68JC> does this seem good with Illusionist's Bracers?
Does what? The enchantment?
Oops
<https://media.wizards.com/2017/ust/en_wrIGMOnRfY.png>
I have no clue what this card does...
I keep falling asleep trying to read it.
Lolol
This kind of silliness is what I love. I would kill for this in black border
So it's another version of that other green enchantment with shroud that has win the game...that thing Helix Pinacle.
Is the whole set spoiled today? We're the album?
Neat ep this week, <@U4V5EHQ2G> :)
Thanks :slightly_smiling_face: We figured we'd take a small hit on listens since so much of it was directed at new players, but it was fun to do a show almost entirely answering questions.
I'm consistently surprised the Kaladesh Invention Sol Ring is more expensive than the judge foil
It's prettier.
Huh
OG art all the way for me
That's because you hate beautiful things.
It's part of your charm.
Some of my decks I intentionally try to run only old, white-border, bad art printings in.
It gives the deck a sort of rustic feel.
